PANDA-BRANDYWINE, L.P. REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION SOURCES SERVICE
Panda-Brandywine, L.P. (“Panda-Brandywine”) provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service (“Reactive Power Service”) from a natural gas-fueled electric generating facility located in Prince George’s County, Maryland (“Facility”) in the control area administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. (“PJM”) in order to assist in maintaining transmission voltages within acceptable limits on the PJM transmission system. This FERC Electric Tariff, Original Volume No. 2 sets forth Panda-Brandywine’s revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Power Service from the Facility to PJM, or to an entity authorized to resell such service to PJM, as provided by Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff.
Total charges for any 12-month period will not be less than the sum of the annual charges specified below. This Tariff shall be effective on the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
1. Fixed Capability Component
The annual revenue requirement for the Fixed Capability Component is $842,229.36. The monthly charge is $842,229.36/12 = $70,185.78.
2. Heating Losses Component
The annual revenue requirement for the Heating Losses Component is $69,839.37. The monthly charge is $69,839.37/12 = $5,819.95.
3. Total Revenue Requirement
Total Annual Revenue Requirement is $842,229.36 + $69,839.37 = $912,068.73. Total Monthly Revenue Requirement is $912,068.73/12 = $76,005.73.
LOST OPPORTUNITY COST CHARGE:
By means of the Lost Opportunity Cost Charge, Panda-Brandywine may receive revenues for lost opportunity costs associated with the Facility calculated and distributed in accordance with Section 3.2.3B of Schedule 1 of the Amended and Restated Operating Agreement of PJM Interconnection, L.L.C., as amended from time to time.
EFFECTIVE DATE:
This Tariff is effective June 1, 2011.
